"Abstract The role of a computer network administrator as a network policeman is being debated between private industry, telecommunication carriers, government regulatory agencies, various public interest groups and the courts. In this article William Cook discusses recent trends in network liability and focuses on the Commerce Department's 1990 BITNET letter, the recent federal decision, Cubby v CompuServe, 776 F. Supp. 135 (SDNY 1991) and other recent cases confronting this issue."
